2026-06-10 00:45:46,239 DEBUG Tool call: submit_final_result({'final_result': '## Segment-Level FCF Proxy — Q1 2026 (in millions)\n\nThe FCF proxy is defined as **Segment Adjusted EBITDA minus capital expenditures**.\n\n### Source Data (from SpaceX S-1, three months ended March 31, 2026)\n\n| Segment | Adjusted EBITDA | Capex | FCF Proxy |\n|---------|----------------|-------|-----------|\n| Space | $(351) | $1,052 | **$(1,403)** |\n| Connectivity | $2,087 | $1,332 | **$755** |\n| AI | $(609) | $7,723 | **$(8,332)** |\n\n### Calculation Detail\n\n- **Space FCF Proxy:** $(351) − $1,052 = **$(1,403) million**\n- **Connectivity FCF Proxy:** $2,087 − $1,332 = **$755 million**\n- **AI FCF Proxy:** $(609) − $7,723 = **$(8,332) million**\n\n---\n\n## Years of Connectivity FCF to Fund AI Capex\n\n**Connectivity annualized FCF proxy:** $755M × 4 = **$3,020 million**\n\n**AI capex at Q1 2026 run-rate (annualized):** $7,723M × 4 = **$30,892 million**\n\n**Years required:** $30,892M ÷ $3,020M = **10.23 years**\n\n(Equivalently, $7,723M ÷ $755M = 10.23, since the annualization factor of 4 cancels out.)\n\n---\n\n### Interpretation\n\nIt would take approximately **10.2 years** of Connectivity\'s annualized FCF proxy (at the Q1 2026 run-rate) to fund a single year of AI segment capital expenditures. This highlights the extraordinary capital intensity of the AI segment ($7.7B in Q1 alone) relative to the cash-generation capacity of the Connectivity segment ($755M of segment-level FCF proxy in Q1). Notably, both Space and AI segments are FCF-proxy-negative, with Connectivity as the only segment generating a positive FCF proxy.\n\n### Important Context\n\nAll figures reflect the recast consolidated entity under common-control accounting, which includes xAI (merged February 2, 2026) and X Holdings (merged into xAI March 28, 2025). The AI segment\'s Adjusted EBITDA of $(609) million and capex of $7,723 million in Q1 2026 are driven predominantly by xAI\'s GPU and data-center infrastructure investments.\n\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 (filed May 20, 2026)"\n    }\n  ]\n}'})
